radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix is dilated, measuring 12 mm in greatest dimension with fluid and air. An appendicolith is seen at the origin and a second appendicolith located distally. No free air or free fluid. The lung bases are clear, liver unremarkable, kidneys symmetric without hydronephrosis, normal gallbladder, pancreas, spleen, adrenals, stomach, and small bowel. No pelvic lymphadenopathy. Disc space narrowing and endplate sclerosis at L4-5, no lesions suspicious for malignancy.
